The paper deals with the task of classification and localization of thoracic diseases from chest radiographs using a convolutional neural network (CNN) based attention-guided curriculum learning (AGCL) framework. This work involves computer vision and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
